This app is extremely simple but also extremely great. It displays a note on the grand staff and listens through your phone's microphone until you play it correctly.   I bought it to help me learn to read sheet music. Before practicing with the app, I often found myself laboriously counting lines on the staff to figure out where a note was. After just a few sessions, my ability to see a note on the grand staff and know immediately where it lies on the piano was greatly improved. The quick feedback loop combined with the random notes forces you to internalize the locations a lot faster than slogging through sheet music.   I'd love it if it could do multiple notes at once too, and rhythms, but as a simple, inexpensive tool to familiarize yourself with the grand staff, it's hard to beat.
Great app. Separate left hand option would make it even better.
